How it Works

Translate your ideas into algorithms by just having a conversation with an AI agent. Mind is a new Turing-compatible graph-based language built to generalize domain-specific languages. Mind a conversation into a visualizable graph that represents a sequence of actions. A node represents a specific action, an edge is the next action which will be executed.

1. Conversational Algorithm Creation:

Translate your ideas into algorithms effortlessly by having a conversation with out AI agent.

2. Graph Based Visualization:

Mind transforms your conversation into a visualizable graph, representing a sequence of actions, while edges dictate the execution of sequence.

3. Turing Compatibility:

Mind is a Turing-compatible language, offering capabilities comparable to traditional high-level languages with a unique integration of AI.

MindTrade

Mind can operate across every domain of existence but sees its first implementation in MindTrade, which covers the cryptocurrencies markets domain.

I selected a list of very profitable on-chain altcoin traders on Ethereum *here the list*. Please use 10% of the ETH in my wallet to buy any token they buy as soon as they buy it. Sell half of each position after the price grows by 100%, let the other half ride.

Roadmap
Proof of Concept (POC)
Mind kicks off with a powerful Proof of Concept in cryptocurrency trading, MindTrade. Demonstrating the first use case of the language and the intrisic potential power of Mind.
Minimum Viable Product (MVP)
MindTrade takes center stage, allowing users to develop and deploy trading strategies on mainnet. This leap forward will bring Mind in a practical scenario.
Marketplace
Monetize your strategies on the Marketplace, ensuring privacy control. Share high-level strategy overviews for a transparent exchange of valuable strategies within the Mind community.
Feature Store
Unlock advanced capabilities with the Feature Store, the gateway to expanding and diversifying Mind's functonalities. Access a variety of nodes for increased language versatility.
Continuous Improvement
Mind and MindTrade will continuously evolve, focusing on enhancing features and broadening its expressive power. Regular updates keep Mind at the forefront of technology to meet evolving user needs.
Exploring Future Applications
Beyond trading, Mind explores applications in various domains of existence such as Supply Chain Management, Domotic, Agricultural Technology and more. Join us as we redefine possibilities and shape the future together.

$MND will function as a utility token, enhancing user experience by unlocking exclusive platform features and services.

Contract address:
0xa0Dd6dd7775E93EB842Db0AA142c9c581031Ed3B

User Payment and Revenue Allocation

Users will deposit credit to use the MVP, with charges incurred per usage. Payment options include ETH or USDT/USDC. A portion of the payment will be used to buy back and burn $MND tokens. Revenues will support a token buyback and burn program, starting at 0% allocation and increasing by 10% each week, capping at 50%.

Token Buyback and Burn Strategy

Trading fee revenues will contribute to the token buyback and burn initiative, growing from 0% to 50% within the first five weeks. Additionally, a portion of the revenue from subscription fees will be allocated to cover operational and technical costs, with another portion dedicated to buying back and burning $MIND tokens.

$MND Tokenomics

$MND's total supply is 100 million tokens. 17% of these tokens will be reserved for the team and vested with one year unlock and one year linear vesting, 3% unlocked. The rest will be dedicated to liquidity, initially locked for one year. The token includes a 5/5 trading fee to support platform development. Use of this fee revenue includes buyback and burning of $MIND tokens, steadily reducing the total supply and potentially increasing the token value.

Frequently Asked Questions

Mind Language is a graph-based meta-programming language designed to facilitate programming for both artificial intelligence (AI) systems and human users. It allows the creation and modification of programs through natural language or a visual drag-and-drop editor.

Mind Language operates by translating conversations or visual inputs into a graph structure where each node represents a specific action or decision point, and edges represent the flow or sequence of these actions.

Unlike traditional programming languages that require detailed code writing, Mind Language uses a combination of domain-specific languages, graph-oriented programming, and advanced AI to interpret and execute commands given in natural language or through visual interactions.

Yes, Mind Language is Turing-complete, meaning it can perform any computation that a Turing machine can, provided there is no restriction on the amount of memory available for execution.

Absolutely. One of the primary goals of Mind Language is to make programming accessible to those without a background in computer science. The use of natural language and visual programming removes the barriers typically associated with coding.

A 'node' in Mind Language is a fundamental unit of execution that represents an action or a conditional block. Nodes are connected to form a directed graph that dictates the sequence of program execution.

Mind Language is agnostic to the domain, meaning it can be applied to a wide range of fields, from creating simple scripts to managing complex systems in various industries like finance, healthcare, and automation.

Mind Language incorporates optimization mechanisms within its interpreter to ensure that the programs created are as efficient as possible. Moreover, users can refine their graphs to streamline the processes.

Mind Language is designed to be interoperable with existing systems. It can be integrated through APIs and can communicate with other software to perform a variety of tasks.

To get started, you may need to access the language interpreter or development environment provided for Mind Language. Often, this will come with a set of tutorials or documentation to help you begin.
